laboratory_examinations.findings: Lower Thorax: No pleural effusion. Liver: Diffuse mild hepatic steatosis with an estimated fat fraction of 9% and a small 1 cm cyst. Biliary: Minimal intrahepatic and extra biliary ductal dilatation up to the ampulla without findings of stricture or focal lesion. Gallbladder contains sludge. No choledocholithiasis or significant stricture. Pancreas: Unremarkable. Spleen: Unremarkable. Adrenal Glands: 1.2 x 1.0 cm right adrenal adenoma. Kidneys: No hydronephrosis, unremarkable except for a few simple renal cysts bilaterally. Gastrointestinal Tract: Juxtapapillary duodenal diverticulum noted and a small to moderate hiatal hernia. No bowel obstruction. Lymph Nodes: No lymphadenopathy in the upper abdomen. Vasculature: Hepatic vasculature is patent. Osseous and Soft Tissue Structures: No suspicious osseous lesion.
